<h2>Arizona Winter School 2017: Perfectoid Spaces</h2>

<p>
    AWS 2017 will be held March 11-15, 2017 at the
    University of Arizona in Tucson, AZ.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        Registration will open September 19.
        <br>
        The deadline to apply for funding is <b>November 11, 2016</b>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Speakers:
      <ul>
        <li><b><a href="http://www-personal.umich.edu/~bhattb/">Bhargav Bhatt</a></b>: p-adic Hodge theory</li>
        <li><b><a href="http://www.math.uni-bonn.de/people/caraiani/">Ana Caraiani</a></b>: Shimura varieties</li>
        <li><b><a href="http://www.kskedlaya.org/">Kiran Kedlaya</a></b>: Sheaves, stacks, and shtukas</li>
        <li><b><a href="http://math.bu.edu/people/jsweinst/">Jared Weinstein</a></b>: Adic spaces</li>
      </ul>
      with opening and closing lectures by <b><a href="http://www.math.uni-bonn.de/people/scholze/">Peter Scholze</a></b>
      
    </li>
    <li>
      Organizers: Bryden Cais and Kiran Kedlaya (main program),
      with Alina Bucur, Mirela Ciperiani, Romyar Sharifi, and David Zureick-Brown.
    </li>
</ul>
